  "texts": [
    "ENMA performs uncertainty estimation by sampling multiple trajectories from its continuous latent space through flow matching.",
    "Unlike discrete autoregressive baselines such as Zebra, which rely on categorical sampling, ENMA's continuous formulation yields sharper and better-calibrated probabilistic forecasts.",
    "As shown in table 4, ENMA achieves the lowest calibration (RM-SCE) and probabilistic (CRPS) errors, confirming its ability to produce both reliable and diverse uncertainty estimates.",
    "Data generation.",
    "We further assess ENMA's ability to generate full trajectories without conditioning on the initial state or PDE parameters."
  ]
}